void storePassword(string username, string userPassword) <br>
{<br>
  string passwordHash = MD5Hash(userPassword);<br>
  WritePasswordFileEntry(username, passwordHash);<br>
  return;<br>
}<br>
<br>
If I was running a board and I wanted to steal passwords, I would never attempt to reverse the MD5.  I'd simply hack the board code to look like this:<br>
<br>
void storePassword(string username, string userPassword) <br>
{<br>
/*  string passwordHash; - commented out */<br>
/*    passwordHash = MD5(userPassword); */<br>
/*    WritePasswordFileEntry(username, passwordHash); */<br>
